4.00	PZT	Lead zirconate titanate	Lead zirconate titanate is an inorganic compound with the chemical formula Pb O3 0≤x≤1). Also called PZT, it is a ceramic perovskite material that shows a marked piezoelectric effect, which find practical applications in the area of electroceramics. It is a white solid that is insoluble in all solvents.	
